-- National Security Adviser Jones Visits India Before Obama's November Trip
-- Kartik Goyal
-- 2010-07-10T09:21:26Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-10/national-security-adviser-jones-visits-india-before-obama-s-november-trip.html

          
          
             U.S. National Security Adviser
General  Jim Jones  is traveling to India this week to prepare
for a visit by President Barack Obama in November.  
 Jones will meet Indian counterpart Shivshankar Menon
during a three-day stay starting July 14 to discuss issues
including counter-terrorism cooperation, regional security,
defense cooperation and export controls, National Security
Council spokesman  Mike Hammer  said in a statement dated
yesterday.  
